quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  37,114,We assuredly bestowed Our favor also upon Moses and Aaron
  37,115,And We saved them and their people from the mighty distress (of slavery and persecution)
  37,116,"And We helped them, so they became the victors"
  37,117,"And We granted them both (Moses and Aaron) the clear Book (which explained the matters that had been secret, and which the people needed for the happiness of their life in both worlds)"
  37,118,We showed them the Straight Path (enabling them to follow it in every matter without any deviance)
  37,119,"And We left for them among later-comers (until the end of time, this greeting and remembrance of them and their Message)"
  37,120,Peace be upon Moses and Aaron
  37,121,Thus do We reward those devoted to doing good as if seeing God
  37,122,Surely those two were among Our truly believing servants
  37,123,And surely Ilyas (Elijah) was one of the Messengers
  37,124,"(Remember) when he said to his people: \"Will you not keep from disobedience to God in reverence for Him and piety"
  37,125,Will you continue to invoke Ba‘l (as deity) and forsake the Creator Who creates everything in the best and most appropriate form and has the ultimate rank of creativity –
  37,126,"God, your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers"
  37,127,"But they denied him, and so they are surely bound to be arraigned (for judgment)"
  37,128,"Except God’s servants, endowed with sincerity in faith and practicing the Religion"
  37,129,And We left for him among later-comers (until the end of time this greeting and remembrance of him and his Message)
  37,130,Peace be upon Il-Yasin
  37,131,Thus do We reward those devoted to doing good as if seeing God
  37,132,Surely he was one of Our truly believing servants
  37,133,And surely Lot was one of the Messengers
  37,134,(Remember) when We (ordered him to leave the land of sinners and) saved him and his family all together
  37,135,Except an old woman among those who stayed behind
  37,136,Then We annihilated the others
  37,137,"Indeed, you pass by them (the ruins of their dwellings) at morning-time (during your travels for trade)"
  37,138,"And by night. Will you not, then, use your reason and take heed"